abstract: Tunisia’s moderate Islamist political party emerges as the acknowledged leader in elections for a constitutional assembly; begins talks to form a unity government with a coalition of liberals in a rare alliance that party leaders are hailing as an inclusive model for countries emerging from the tumult of the Arab Spring.
snippet: Ennahda began talks to form a unity government with a coalition of liberals in a rare alliance that party leaders hailed as a model for other Arab countries.
